    "rule": "Every figure carries a state government source. Estate tax is modeled as the top marginal rate on the amount over the exemption (the graduated lower brackets are an approximation, flagged in copy). Inheritance heir-class rates are the top rate for that class.",
    "reviewerFlags": [
      "WA: split-year 2026 — 35% top rate for deaths Jan-Jun, 20% Jul onward; exemption ~$3,076,000. estateTopRate stored as 0.35 (H1); note explains.",
      "NY: 'cliff' — estates over 105% of the exemption are taxed from dollar one. Not modeled; flagged in the note.",
      "Indexed exemptions (CT, ME, NY, RI, DC, WA) change yearly; fixed ones (HI, IL, MD, MA, MN, OR, VT) do not.",
      "Estate tax uses top-rate-over-exemption; true schedules are graduated, so figures are approximate for smaller taxable estates."
    ],
    "heirClasses": "spouse / lineal (children, parents, grandchildren) / sibling / other. Rates are the top marginal rate for that class; 0 means exempt."
